      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "KUNAMA NAMADGI (1) was never in contention last time at Sandown, but prior to that won by 1.75 lengths at this track (28.53) beating Greysynd Bonnie in a Bottom Up - Grade 6 on March 3. Looks the one to beat on her best form. KRAKEN SCOOBY (3) turned in a plain run last time when sixth at Shepparton over 450m behind Motivate (26.15) in a Bottom Up - Grade 5. Was a winner the start prior. Has ability and can measure up. AUNTIE AMBER (8) doesn't win out of turn but recent form sound. Finished second (25.66) at Shepparton last time making it three minors on end. Has a good record at this journey. Ran one of the fastest times on the program last start despite finishing in the minors. Winning chance. TORNADO JACK (4) is worth another chance despite missing the top-three here most recently.",
